id: pm-rjqr
title: "Promote query/read primitives to the public SDK: list, get, search, context, next, aggregate, stats"
description: "Typed SDK read surface over the item store, search (keyword/semantic/hybrid incl. inline field:value parsing), context snapshots, next-item recommendation, aggregates, and stats. History/activity ownership is pm-4a7m. Duplicate check: no existing query-primitive SDK item."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: architecture,"area:sdk","area:search"
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:54:09.542Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T02:53:35.167Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: SDK exports typed query primitives returning the same data the CLI renders (projection/format concerns stay CLI-side); CLI query commands consume only these primitives; docstrings + linked tests + SDK reference docs; zero behavior change (query/search specs green)
parent: pm-usfg
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: "PmClient and SDK top-level exports now expose list, get, search, context, next, aggregate, and stats read primitives with tests and docs. CLI read handlers remain on native extension-aware runners while SDK consumers use the shared in-process action path."
expected_result: Package authors and agents can use stable SDK read primitives for context management without subprocess coupling.
actual_result: "SDK read primitives, structured create payloads, lifecycle wrappers, docs, installed-package dogfood, and full coverage all passed; extension-aware CLI behavior remains intact."
