  "2026-07-07T02:15:38.787Z",codex-sdk-primitives-agent,"PR #477 review-loop evidence: after bundling SDK read primitives, structured create payloads, SDK lifecycle mutations, SDK package-coordinate docs, and lifecycle alias ergonomics into one PR, addressed additional CodeRabbit/Cubic feedback by centralizing hidden Commander option registration, rejecting conflicting lifecycle --author/--assignee inputs, strengthening composite lifecycle alias tests, and adding command-doc tracker references. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/register-commands.spec.ts; pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (5448 tests, 100/100/100/100)."
  "2026-07-07T02:36:31.023Z",codex-sdk-primitives-agent,"PR #477 Greptile review-loop evidence: fixed SDK/MCP compound start-task and pause-task alias leakage by stripping the lifecycle-only assignee alias before forwarding options to runUpdate, while preserving the alias for claim/release ownership resolution. Added regression coverage for client default author precedence when assignee alias differs. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts; pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (5448 tests, 100/100/100/100)."
  "2026-07-07T02:53:35.167Z",codex-sdk-primitives-agent,"PR #477 final Greptile follow-up: SDK lifecycle/read bundle now also fixes restore projection parity for fullChangedFields/idOnly through shared mutation projection. Verification passed: SDK focused tests, typecheck, lint, and full coverage 100/100/100/100."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T14:07:53.915Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-06 audit #12 external verification: installed the packed 2026.7.6 tarball in a fresh CJS host project and exercised the promoted read primitives via dynamic import of @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk — list/get/search/context/next/stats all returned correct results against a sandbox tracker (get/search take positional id/query + options + clientOptions). PmClient create/update/close round-trip also verified from CJS. One DX note: raw client.run('create', {type,title}) fails 'Missing required option --title' (args must be pre-split); typed client.create() is the working path — consider mapping bare title/type in run() args or documenting the split contract."
